{
  "verses": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "text": [
        "The Prophet’s Afflictions"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "1",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I am the man who has seen afflictionunder the rod of God’s wrath."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "2",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He has driven me away and made me walkin darkness instead of light."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "3",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Indeed, He keeps turning His handagainst me all day long."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "4",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He has worn away my flesh and skin; He has shattered my bones."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "5",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He has besieged me and surrounded mewith bitterness and hardship."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "6",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He has made me dwell in darknesslike those dead for ages."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "7",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He has walled me in so I cannot escape; He has weighed me down with chains."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "8",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Even when I cry out and plead for help, He shuts out my prayer."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "9",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He has barred my ways with cut stones; He has made my paths crooked."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "10",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He is a bear lying in wait, a lion hiding in ambush."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "11",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He forced me off my path and tore me to pieces; He left me without help."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "12",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He bent His bow and set me as the target for His arrow."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "13",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He pierced my kidneyswith His arrows."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "14",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I am a laughingstock to all my people; they mock me in song all day long."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "15",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He has filled me with bitterness; He has intoxicated me with wormwood."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "16",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He has ground my teeth with gravel and trampled me in the dust."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "17",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "My soul has been deprived of peace; I have forgotten what prosperity is."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "18",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "So I say,"
        },
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "My strength has perished, along with my hope from the LORD.",
          "speaker": "Unknown"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "text": [
        "The Prophet’s Hope"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "19",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Remember my affliction and wandering, the wormwood and the gall."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "20",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Surely my soul remembers and is humbled within me."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "21",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Yet I call this to mind, and therefore I have hope:"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "22",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Because of the loving devotion of the LORD we are not consumed, for His mercies never fail."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "23",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "They are new every morning; great is Your faithfulness!"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "24",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "The LORD is my portion,",
          "speaker": "Jeremiah"
        },
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "says my soul,"
        },
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "therefore I will hope in Him.",
          "speaker": "Unknown"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "25",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "The LORD is good to those who wait for Him, to the soul who seeks Him."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "26",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "It is good to wait quietlyfor the salvation of the LORD."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "27",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "It is good for a man to bear the yokewhile he is still young."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "28",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Let him sit alone in silence, for God has disciplined him."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "29",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Let him bury his face in the dust—perhaps there is still hope."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "30",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Let him offer his cheek to the one who would strike him; let him be filled with reproach."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "31",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "For the Lord will notcast us off forever."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "32",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Even if He causes grief, He will show compassionaccording to His abundant loving devotion."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "33",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "For He does not willingly afflictor grieve the sons of men."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "34",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "To crush underfootall the prisoners of the land,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "35",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "to deny a man justicebefore the Most High,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "36",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "to subvert a man in his lawsuit—of these the Lord does not approve."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "text": [
        "God’s Justice"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "37",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Who has spoken and it came to pass, unless the Lord has ordained it?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "38",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Do not both adversity and goodcome from the mouth of the Most High?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "39",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Why should any mortal man complain, in view of his sins?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "40",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Let us examine and test our ways, and turn back to the LORD."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "41",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Let us lift up our hearts and handsto God in heaven:"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "42",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "prayer",
          "text": "We have sinned and rebelled; You have not forgiven.",
          "speaker": "Unknown"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "43",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "You have covered Yourself in anger and pursued us; You have killed without pity."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "44",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "You have covered Yourself with a cloudthat no prayer can pass through."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "45",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "You have made us scum and refuseamong the nations."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "46",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "All our enemiesopen their mouths against us."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "47",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Panic and pitfall have come upon us—devastation and destruction."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "48",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Streams of tears flow from my eyesover the destruction of the daughter of my people."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "49",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "My eyes overflow unceasingly, without relief,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "50",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "until the LORDlooks down from heaven and sees."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "51",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "My eyes bring grief to my soulbecause of all the daughters of my city."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "52",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Without cause my enemieshunted me like a bird."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "53",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "They dropped me alive into a pit and cast stones upon me."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "54",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "The waters flowed over my head, and I thought I was going to die."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "55",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I called on Your name, O LORD, out of the depths of the Pit."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "56",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "You heard my plea:"
        },
        {
          "type": "prayer",
          "text": "Do not ignore my cry for relief.",
          "speaker": "Unknown"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "57",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "You drew near when I called on You; You said,"
        },
        {
          "type": "divine",
          "text": "Do not be afraid.",
          "speaker": "The LORD"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "58",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "You defend my cause, O Lord; You redeem my life."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "59",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "You have seen, O LORD, the wrong done to me; vindicate my cause!"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "60",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "You have seen all their malice, all their plots against me."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "61",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "O LORD, You have heard their insults, all their plots against me—"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "62",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "the slander and murmuring of my assailantsagainst me all day long."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "63",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "When they sit and when they rise, see how they mock me in song."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "64",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "You will pay them back what they deserve, O LORD, according to the work of their hands."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "65",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Put a veil of anguish over their hearts; may Your curse be upon them!"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "66",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "You will pursue them in anger and exterminate themfrom under Your heavens, O LORD."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    }
  ]
}